01:09.669 --> 01:12.839 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: All that and more on
tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:12.872 --> 01:17.277 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:17.310 --> 01:30.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: We begin tonight with
a report
that President Trump urged
then-FBI Director

01:30.790 --> 01:37.197 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
James Comey to drop the
investigation of one
of his campaign aides'
connections to Russia.

01:37.230 --> 01:42.435 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The New York Times reports that,
at a February
meeting, Mr. Trump told Comey,
"I hope you

01:42.469 --> 01:44.270 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
can let this go."

01:44.304 --> 01:49.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It came the day after the
president fired
National Security Adviser
Michael Flynn for

01:49.242 --> 01:51.678 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
lying about his contacts with
the Russians.

01:51.711 --> 01:54.814 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The president fired Comey last
week.

01:54.848 --> 02:00.620 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
