problematic for
the White House.

05:19.052 --> 05:24.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Matt Apuzzo, as you
say, this could
be a dramatic turning point in
this relationship

05:24.090 --> 05:27.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and what is going on between the
two men,
between President Trump and
James Comey.

05:27.660 --> 05:28.628 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thanks for joining us.

05:28.661 --> 05:29.629 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MATT APUZZO: Great to be here.

05:29.662 --> 05:31.431 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thanks so much.

05:31.464 --> 05:34.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And, meanwhile, the
White House
is also standing its ground
tonight in the

05:34.434 --> 05:37.670 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
other uproar swirling around
President Trump
today.

05:37.704 --> 05:42.575 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At issue in that case,
allegations that he
passed along classified
intelligence from

05:42.608 --> 05:44.877 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
another nation to the Russians.

05:44.911 --> 05:46.746 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William Brangham begins our
coverage.

05:46.779 --> 05:49.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
H.R. MCMASTER, U.S. National
Security Adviser:
What the president discussed
with the foreign

05:49.315 --> 05:54.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
