14:50.856 --> 14:55.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, secondly, I think he has an
obligation
under his oath as president of
the United

14:56.028 --> 14:59.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
States, when he in his judgment
determines
it's in the best interests of
the people of

14:59.598 --> 15:03.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the United States, to declassify
something
and do it.

15:03.168 --> 15:06.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The national media has treated
this story
as if this was a one-off, like
this never

15:06.772 --> 15:08.641 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
happens.

15:08.674 --> 15:11.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Look, the president of the
United States deals
every day with heads of other
countries, with

15:11.210 --> 15:13.379 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
high-level people of other
countries.

15:13.412 --> 15:17.983 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he constantly discusses
classified information
with them.

15:18.017 --> 15:19.952 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Not only can he do that.

15:19.985 --> 15:24.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He should do that, because we
exchange classified
information with almost every
country on the

15:24.757 --> 15:27.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
face of the Earth, with the
exception of a
couple of them.

15:27.993 --> 15:33.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we -- even ones that we're
not particularly
friendly with, we do have
overlapping interests

15:33.699 --> 15:36.168 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in things like airline safety.

15:36.201 --> 15:41.774 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so if, indeed, that was the
subject, and
that's what's been reported, he
should be

15:41.807 --> 15:42.875 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
commended for that.

15:42.908 --> 15:45.311 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The real story here is, there's
a weasel here.

15:45.344 --> 15:49.848 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that is the person who
reported about
this conversation.

15:49.882 --> 15:52.418 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is a person who is a
traitor.

15:52.451 --> 15:55.087 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They betrayed their own country.

15:55.120 --> 15:57.723 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They betrayed their families and
their neighbors.

15:57.756 --> 16:04.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when you disclose classified
information,
classified conversations that
you have access

16:04.830 --> 16:07.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to, it is an act of treason.

16:07.399 --> 16:10.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's unfortunate we can't get
that person
identified.

16:10.069 --> 16:16.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he or she should be held to
answer for
that and treated as any
treasonous person

16:16.075 --> 16:17.910 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
would be.

16:17.943 --> 16:20.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Senator, you say that
the president
can declassify any information,
any classified

16:20.679 --> 16:21.914 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
information.

16:21.947 --> 16:24.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I understand that's true for
U.S. intelligence
products.

16:24.183 --> 16:28.654 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But this was an intelligence --
intelligence
developed by another country.

16:28.687 --> 16:33.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Can he also declassify material
given by another
country's intelligence service?

16:33.892 --> 16:34.860 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

16:34.893 --> 16:36.428 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES RISCH: Of course.

16:36.462 --> 16:41.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We don't even have laws that
cover classified
information from another
country.

16:41.500 --> 16:45.304 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
People could talk about that
wherever they
want to.

16:45.337 --> 16:46.739 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You don't generally do that.

16:46.772 --> 16:48.974 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You treat like it all other
classified information.

16:49.008 --> 16:54.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the president of the United
States is
fully entitled to discuss this
with the people

16:54.079 --> 16:55.948 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
he sees fit to do it.

16:55.981 --> 16:58.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Senator, you're
chairman of the
subcommittee -- Senate Foreign
Affairs Subcommittee

16:58.417 --> 16:59.385 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on the Near East.

16:59.418 --> 17:00.386 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

17:00.419 --> 17:01.453 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES RISCH: I am.

17:01.487 --> 17:02.955 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

17:02.988 --> 17:04.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The reports are that
this information
product came from Israel.

17:04.723 --> 17:10.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Does it give you any concern or
any pause
that this was given to Russia,
an ally of

17:10.295 --> 17:13.665 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
