existential
threat?

17:13.699 --> 17:15.434 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

17:15.467 --> 17:17.803 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES RISCH: Yes, well, first of
all, like
I said, if it was what's been
reported on,

17:17.836 --> 17:22.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that is airline safety, it would
have nothing
to do with the relationship
between Iran and

17:22.541 --> 17:25.444 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIS and Hezbollah and all that
sort of thing.

17:25.477 --> 17:30.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But my position is exactly the
same as the
Israeli ambassador, who was
asked about this

17:30.149 --> 17:34.686 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
early today and said this will
have absolutely
no effect on the great
cooperation between

17:34.720 --> 17:39.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the security and intelligence
agencies of
the United States of America and
Israel.

17:39.825 --> 17:41.794 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We have been very close.

17:41.827 --> 17:43.695 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're going to continue to be
very close.

17:43.729 --> 17:45.631 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have concurrent interests.

17:45.664 --> 17:51.503 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, look, there's been other
times where
there have been embarrassing
lapses and disclosures,

17:51.537 --> 17:53.238 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and we have worked around it.

17:53.272 --> 17:55.841 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's not uncommon in these
kinds of
things.

