SEN.

18:04.216 --> 18:06.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES RISCH: Right.

18:06.085 --> 18:08.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: ... is there a
concern that there
was enough information in what
the president

18:08.253 --> 18:13.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
said that the Russians could
figure out the
methods and sources and put that
source at

18:13.492 --> 18:14.460 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
risk?

18:14.493 --> 18:16.261 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

18:16.295 --> 18:20.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES RISCH: Almost never are
methods and
sources disclosed, unless there
is a reason

18:20.499 --> 18:24.903 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to do that, such as an asset
would be at risk
or someone's life is at risk.

18:24.937 --> 18:30.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, it wouldn't be unusual that
the president
did or didn't know what the
methods and sources

18:30.242 --> 18:31.944 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
were.

18:31.977 --> 18:36.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's just -- it's part of this
anti-Trump
fervor that the national media
has to try

18:36.248 --> 18:39.251 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to make him look bad every time
he turns around.

18:39.284 --> 18:42.654 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This was a good act that he did,
not a bad
act that he did.

18:42.688 --> 18:44.790 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But there was a bad act done
here.

18:44.823 --> 18:50.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Somebody ought to go to the --
to the people
who printed this and say, look,
you're an

18:50.262 --> 18:51.230 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
American.

18:51.263 --> 18:52.364 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm an American.

18:52.397 --> 18:54.199 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tell us who did this, so we can
put them in
jail.

18:54.233 --> 18:57.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Senator James Risch
of the Senate
Intelligence Committee, thanks
so much for

18:57.202 --> 18:58.170 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
joining us.

18:58.203 --> 18:59.171 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

18:59.204 --> 19:01.340 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JAMES RISCH: Thank you, John.

19:01.373 --> 19:04.910 align:left position:0%,start line:66.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Now for some insights
on this apparent
disclosure, and the wider
effects on
intelligence-gathering

19:04.943 --> 19:09.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and sharing, I'm joined by two
men with deep
knowledge of the U.S.
intelligence community

19:09.982 --> 19:12.684 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and the partnerships it relies
upon.

19:12.718 --> 19:18.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
James Woolsey served as director
of the CIA
from early 1993 until January
1995.

19:18.957 --> 19:22.528 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was an adviser to President
Trump's campaign
last year.

19:22.561 --> 19:28.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Andrew Exum, he was former
deputy assistant
secretary of defense for Middle
East policy

19:28.100 --> 19:29.701 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in the Obama administration.

19:29.735 --> 19:32.037 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He's also a former Army Ranger.

19:32.070 --> 19:33.772 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Mr. Woolsey, let me start with
you.

19:33.805 --> 19:36.909 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You heard Senator Risch say this
was a good
thing the president did, not a
bad thing.

19:36.942 --> 19:38.644 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Do you agree?

19:38.677 --> 19:41.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES WOOLSEY, Former CIA
Director: Well,
it depends on whether the
information gets

19:41.480 --> 19:50.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
out and damages our -- either
our relations
with another country or our
ability to keep

19:50.923 --> 19:53.625 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
sources and methods held very
closely.

19:53.659 --> 20:00.132 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It may be that it will not cause
a major difficulty.

20:00.165 --> 20:08.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think giving anything away
to the Russians
is something that has to pass
about half-a-dozen

20:08.640 --> 20:10.509 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
levels of scrutiny.

20:10.542 --> 20:13.312 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's the real problem
here.

20:13.345 --> 20:19.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Unlike President Reagan, who was
faced with
declassification decisions on
the aircraft

20:19.318 --> 20:25.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that was shot down, the Russian
aircraft,
and so forth, here, we have just
turned it

20:25.557 --> 20:28.126 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
loose, and to the Russians.

20:28.160 --> 20:34.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that ought to have been
preceded by a
day or two anyway of high-level
discussions

20:34.700 --> 20:38.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
among top-level officials to
make sure we
knew exactly what we were
turning loose and

20:38.470 --> 20:39.438 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
exactly why.

20:39.471 --> 20:41.240 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Andrew, what's your
take on this?

20:41.273 --> 20:42.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDREW EXUM, Former U.S. Deputy
Assistant
Secretary of Defense: Well, no,
that's exactly

20:42.207 --> 20:44.076 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
right.

20:44.109 --> 20:47.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With all due respect to the
senator from Idaho,
any time -- and, look, I just
came out of

20:47.512 --> 20:49.248 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
government service at the
Pentagon.

20:49.281 --> 20:53.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I know how frustrating leaks can
be, but any
time someone says the real
problem is the

20:53.518 --> 20:56.488 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
media or leaks, they're usually
trying to
defend the indefensible.

20:56.521 --> 21:01.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the problem here is that I
don't think
the American people realize how
much of our

21:01.693 --> 21:05.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
intelligence is actually derived
from our
partners.

21:05.497 --> 21:11.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If our partners cannot feel or
do not trust
that our president will not
divulge that information

21:11.637 --> 21:16.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to, I mean, goodness gracious,
the Russians
in this case, then that could
create real

21:16.174 --> 21:18.243 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
problems for us going forward.

21:18.277 --> 21:21.947 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I completely agree with
everything that
Director Woolsey said.

21:21.980 --> 21:26.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that this is a broader
problem, regardless
of how bad the actual leak was.

21:26.985 --> 21:30.188 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And when you were in
the Obama
administration, there was a lot
of debate

21:30.222 --> 21:33.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over how much intelligence over
Syria to give
to the Russians.

21:33.659 --> 21:34.626 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANDREW EXUM: Yes, there sure
was.

21:34.660 --> 21:36.261 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: What were the issues?

21:36.295 --> 21:38.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, we heard Mr. Woolsey say
you have
got to go through a lot of
checkpoints.

21:38.897 --> 21:41.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What were the considerations you
went through
on that?

21:41.099 --> 21:43.001 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANDREW EXUM: Well, that's
exactly right.

21:43.035 --> 21:46.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You talk to anybody in the
intelligence community,
and you say, we want to release
some information

21:47.005 --> 21:51.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the Russians, first off,
making something
secret releasable to Russia is
almost a contradiction

21:51.510 --> 21:55.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in terms, because so many of the
sources and
methods that we have developed
over decades

21:55.881 --> 21:58.450 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are really to allow us to spy on
the Russians.

21:58.483 --> 22:00.319 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's from the Cold War.

22:00.352 --> 22:05.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, there's a lot of worry that,
even in divulge
anything type of information to
the Russians,

22:05.090 --> 22:10.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
even if you don't get into
sources and methods,
they're going to
backwards-engineer how you

22:10.262 --> 22:14.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
got that information, and thus
learn something
about your own capabilities.

22:14.266 --> 22:19.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So that was a huge concern any
time you start
to discuss sharing information
with the Russians.

22:19.171 --> 22:23.809 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And, Mr. Woolsey,
there are reports
now that this information came
from Israel.

22:23.842 --> 22:29.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is that a particular concern of
giving this
information to Russia, who is
allied with

22:29.848 --> 22:34.953 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Iran, who Israel sees as a
mortal threat to
their existence?

22:34.986 --> 22:39.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES WOOLSEY: Yes, but there's
a major footnote,
I think.

22:39.124 --> 22:42.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The yes is because of the way
you formed the
question.

22:42.094 --> 22:50.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yes, it is a serious matter if
it undercuts
Israel's security at all and if
it disturbs

22:50.502 --> 22:53.105 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
our relations with them.

22:53.138 --> 23:00.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the Israelis, looking at the
shift from
President Obama to President
Trump, would

23:00.946 --> 23:06.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
probably give up a couple of
half-ton trucks
full of classified information
in order to

23:06.218 --> 23:08.453 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
preserve that switch.

23:08.487 --> 23:14.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they are very happy with --
and understandably
so, with the new American
administration.

23:14.626 --> 23:18.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And although they would have
criticisms, and
if there was something really
sensitive in

23:18.597 --> 23:23.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this, they would have been very
upset about
it and would have come in and
talked to the

23:23.602 --> 23:27.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
American director of central
intelligence
and explained why they were
really worried

23:27.139 --> 23:29.207 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and it ought not to happen
again.

23:29.241 --> 23:36.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But in terms of quietly seething
and being
really upset and so forth, no,
they're -- I

23:36.648 --> 23:39.618 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
think they're very pleased at
having a Trump
administration.

23:39.651 --> 23:43.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Woolsey, General
McMaster said
that he -- that the president
didn't know

23:43.188 --> 23:45.524 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
where this information came
from.

23:45.557 --> 23:52.631 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're experienced at briefing
presidents,
and also, quite frankly,
briefing this president.

23:52.664 --> 23:54.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You worked with him in the
campaign.

23:54.566 --> 23:59.337 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How much information do you give
a president
about a piece of intelligence?

23:59.371 --> 24:05.944 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES WOOLSEY: Well, I think in
a circumstance
in which he has to make a
decision to disclose

24:05.977 --> 24:12.451 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
it to some government or
individual that would
be a serious potential problem,
such as to

24:12.484 --> 24:21.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russia, I think you owe him a
very thorough
understanding, and you ought not
to just send

24:21.092 --> 24:22.928 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the paper in as part of a
document.

24:22.961 --> 24:31.970 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
You ought to have enough
leverage over his
schedule to have the time to
say, Mr. President,

24:32.003 --> 24:36.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I hope you haven't decided to
turn any of
this loose, but should you be
thinking about

24:36.074 --> 24:41.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that, the way you were back a
few weeks ago,
here are the problems with
turning anything

24:41.746 --> 24:45.750 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
loose on this subject and on
this subject
and on this subject.

24:45.784 --> 24:48.954 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He deserves a really thorough
scrubbing.

24:48.987 --> 24:56.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Andrew Exum, so, talk
about, what
is the potential threat to
intelligence gathering

24:56.161 --> 24:57.128 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the future?

24:57.162 --> 24:58.997 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ANDREW EXUM: Yes.

24:59.030 --> 25:00.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, first off, I think that
Director Woolsey
is probably right in terms of
talking about

25:00.732 --> 25:05.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the way in which the Israeli
prime minister
views the switch from Obama to
Trump.

25:05.103 --> 25:09.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I don't necessarily think he's
speaking for
the Israeli defense and
intelligence establishment.

25:09.608 --> 25:15.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think, there, there is a lot
of unease,
precisely because, between 2009
and 2017,

25:15.113 --> 25:19.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we dramatically increased the
amount of military
and intelligence cooperation
with the Israelis.

25:19.985 --> 25:24.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I suspect that you are going
to see a
lot of unease within the Israeli
intelligence

25:24.122 --> 25:25.891 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and defense establishment.

25:25.924 --> 25:30.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're already starting to see
quotes from
Israelis nervous about what has
potentially

25:30.195 --> 25:32.030 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
transpired.

25:32.063 --> 25:35.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, there, I think the worry
going forward
is that, not just with the
Israelis, but with

25:35.934 --> 25:40.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
all of our partners, there's
just going to
be a reluctance to hand over
information to

25:40.138 --> 25:46.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Americans, especially if
it's sensitive,
because, frankly, under our
system, any secret

25:46.278 --> 25:48.079 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is the president's.

25:48.113 --> 25:51.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president -- you know,
things are classified
at his discretion and at his
pleasure.

25:51.049 --> 25:55.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, legally, the president can
do exactly
what he potentially did a few
days ago in

25:55.420 --> 25:58.056 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
terms of releasing information
to the Russians.

25:58.089 --> 26:04.763 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that that's going to be
problematic,
to say the least, for many of
our partners,

26:04.796 --> 26:07.632 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not only in the region, but
elsewhere around
the globe.

26:07.666 --> 26:09.401 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JAMES WOOLSEY: I agree with
that.

26:09.434 --> 26:11.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: I know we could talk
much more
about this, but I'm afraid we're
out of time.

26:11.369 --> 26:12.604 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have got to leave it there.

26:12.637 --> 26:14.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Andrew Exum, James Woolsey,
thank you both
for joining us.

26:14.839 --> 26:21.146 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JAMES WOOLSEY: Good to be with
you.

26:21.179 --> 26:31.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: In the day's other
news: Syria
denied U.S. claims that it's
using a crematorium

26:31.056 --> 26:34.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to conceal mass executions of
thousands of
prisoners.

26:34.893 --> 26:40.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Foreign Ministry called it
categorically
false and said it's a new
Hollywood plot to

26:40.432 --> 26:42.334 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
justify American intervention.

26:42.367 --> 26:47.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The State Department accused
Syria of incinerating
the corpses of executed
prisoners to destroy

26:47.839 --> 26:51.610 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
